[I] Offers a series of D-Bus services to index filesystem resources

[T] Previously known as tracker-miners (tracker3), is the indexer and search
[T] engine that powers the desktop search for core GNOME components. It stores
[T] data about user files structured by the Nepomuk definitions, features a
[T] tightly sandboxed metadata extractor, and provides facilities to alter file
[T] metadata.

[U] https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/localsearch

[A] The GNOME Project <gnome-devel-list@gnome.org>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/office extra/shell extra/desktop/gnome

[L] GPL
[V] 3.11.1

[CV-URL] https://download.gnome.org/sources/localsearch/cache.json
[D] e6d7c18f9ceaece9191f1cc2f8cdfffe6a6891369ded52ccba0695bb localsearch-3.11.1.tar.xz https://download.gnome.org/sources/localsearch/3.11/

. $base/package/*/*/gnome-conf.in
pkginstalled systemd || var_append mesonopt ' ' -Dsystemd_user_services=false
pkginstalled upower || var_append mesonopt ' ' -Dbattery_detection=none
var_append mesonopt ' ' -Dlandlock=disabled
var_append mesonopt ' ' '-Dfunctional_tests=false -Dsandbox_tests=false'
